Class ETPush

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.exacttarget.etpushsdk.ETPush

  • public class ETPush
extends Object
    JB4A SDK main class for MobilePush actions.

    Use configureSdk(ETPushConfig, ETPushConfigureSdkListener) to bootstrap your app with the SDK.

      • configureSdk

        public static void configureSdk(@NonNull
                                ETPushConfig pushConfig,
                                @NonNull
                                ETPushConfigureSdkListener listener)
                         throws ETException
        Parameters:
        pushConfig - ETPushConfig
        listener - ETPushConfigureSdkListener
        Throws:
        ETException - Call this from your Application's Application.onCreate() method. This method initializes ETPush and bootstraps it to your app.

        Use ETPushConfig.Builder to provide details of the SFMC MobilePush app you want to connect with as well as which features to enable within the SDK.

        This method will perform all activities on a background thread and will return immediately.

        configureSdk() must be the first call before calling any other SDK methods or using any other classes.

        The reason we ask that you call this within your Application class is to ensure that background activities performed to display messages will be able to bootstrap to your app.

        ETException

      • getInstance

        public static ETPush getInstance()
                          throws ETException
        Provides an instance of the ETPush class that is prepared for you in configureSdk().

        Before using this method, you must first call configureSdk(ETPushConfig, ETPushConfigureSdkListener) from your Application's Application.onCreate() method.

        Remember that configureSdk() will process all work on a thread. So when you request an instance of ETPush, it must wait for configureSdk() to be completed. Therefore, rather than calling getInstance() immediately after configureSdk() or even in your Launcher Activity, we recommend that you use the ETPush instance returned in the ETPushConfigureSdkListener callback. Alternatively, you could listen for the Event ReadyAimFireInitCompletedEvent. Both methods will prevent Application Not Responding (ANR) messages in your app.

        Returns:
        ETPush singleton getInstance
        Throws:
        ETException

      • activityPaused

        @Deprecated
public static void activityPaused(android.app.Activity activity)
        Deprecated. This method is only needed for Android versions prior to 14 and the minimum supported version for the JB4A SDK is 15.
        Call this method from your Activity's onPause() method for Android versions < 14. Beginning with Android Ice Cream Sandwich (API 14) these callbacks are handled internally.

        The SDK uses these calls to keep track of the open Activities to determine when your app comes into the foreground or is put into the background.

        Several functions within the SDK (such as Analytics, CloudPages, Location) perform actions either when the app comes into the foreground, or when the app is put into the background.

        Failure to call these methods within your Activities will disable functionality you might have been expecting when you bootstrapped your app using configureSdk(ETPushConfig, ETPushConfigureSdkListener).

        Parameters:
        activity - The paused Activity.

      • updateEt

        public void updateEt()
        This method will force a registration call, at most, once every minute. It bypasses the normal 1 min. aggregation of all events that can affect a device/user registration and should be used exceedingly sparingly. If a call to updateEt() is made within 60 seconds of the initial call it will result in a "normal" registration call.

      • addAttribute

        public boolean addAttribute(@NonNull
                            String attribute,
                            @NonNull
                            String value)
                     throws ETException
        Adds a value to a defined attribute within the SFMC Contact model for your customer.

        The attribute must be defined within the SFMC Contact model prior to adding a value. If the attribute does not exist within the SFMC Contact model, then this attribute will be ignored within the SFMC.

        If you previously called addAttribute(String, String) for this attribute, then the value will be updated with the new value and sent to the SFMC.

        All attribute values set with this method persist through the installation of the app on your customer device.

        Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided when setting up new attributes in the SFMC Contact model.

        Parameters:
        attribute - Attribute name as currently defined within the SFMC Contact Model.
        value - Value to assign to that attribute for your customer
        Returns:
        True if successfully added
        Throws:
        ETException

      • removeAttribute

        public void removeAttribute(@NonNull
                            String attribute)
                     throws ETException
        Removes an attribute from the list of attributes created with addAttribute(String, String) from being be sent to the SFMC.

        Note: this method removes the attribute from future sends. It does not change the actual value, nor does it remove it from the SFMC Contact model. It simply means that the last value for this attribute will no longer be sent.

        If you want to set the value within the SFMC Contact model for this attribute to blanks, then you should call addAttribute(String, String) with a blank value. Example:

        addAttribute("First_Name", "");

        Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided when setting up new attributes in the SFMC Contact model.

        Parameters:
        attribute - Attribute name as currently defined within the SFMC Contact Model.
        Throws:
        ETException

        There are three ways to override the notifications displayed when an alert is received. See ETNotifications for complete list.
